@startuml CarRental_Annotated

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam nodesep 35
skinparam ranksep 30
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

skinparam enum {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

skinparam interface {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

title <size:18>Car Rental System (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "User searches for a 4-wheeler at Store#1, reserves it for 3 days, picks up, returns car, bill generated, pays via UPI."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE — VehicleRentalSystem + Store
' ====================================================================
class VehicleRentalSystem <<Facade>> {
    + storeList : vector<Store*>
    + userList : vector<User*>
    --
    + getStore(storeId) : Store*
    + getUser(index) : User*
    + addStore(store) : void
    + addUser(user) : void
}

class Store <<Facade>> {
    - storeId : int
    - storeLocation : Location
    - inventory : VehicleInventoryManager
    - reservationManager : ReservationManager
    - defaultBillingStrategy : DailyBillingStrategy
    - billManager : BillManager
    - defaultPaymentStrategy : UPIPaymentStrategy
    - paymentManager : PaymentManager
    --
    + Store(storeId, location)
    + getVehicles(type, from, to) : vector<Vehicle*>
    + createReservation(vehicleId, user, from, to, type) : Reservation*
    + cancelReservation(reservationId) : void
    + startTrip(reservationId) : void
    + submitVehicle(reservationId) : void
    + generateBill(reservationId, strategy) : Bill*
    + makePayment(bill, strategy, amount) : Payment*
    + getInventory() : VehicleInventoryManager*
}

note top of VehicleRentalSystem #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "**VehicleRentalSystem** is the top-level
    Facade. Manages all stores and users."

    "**Store** is the per-location Facade.
    It composes everything: inventory,
    reservations, billing, payments.
    Client calls: store.getVehicles() ->
    store.createReservation() -> store.startTrip()
    -> store.submitVehicle() -> store.generateBill()
    -> store.makePayment(). One stop for all."
    **Pattern: Facade | SRP, DIP**
end note

VehicleRentalSystem o--> Store : has stores >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: USER + LOCATION + VEHICLE
' ====================================================================
class User {
    + userId : int
    + userName : string
    + drivingLicenseNo : string
    --
    + getUserId() : int
    + getUserName() : string
    + getDrivingLicenseNo() : string
}

class Location {
    + buildingNo : int
    + area : string
    + city : string
    + state : string
    + country : string
    + pincode : int
}

class Vehicle {
    - vehicleID : int
    - vehicleNumber : string
    - vehicleType : VehicleType
    - dailyRentalCost : double
    - vehicleStatus : VehicleStatus
    --
    + getVehicleID() : int
    + getVehicleType() : VehicleType
    + getVehicleStatus() : VehicleStatus
    + getDailyRentalCost() : double
    + setDailyRentalCost(cost) : void
    + setStatus(status) : void
}

enum VehicleType {
    FOUR_WHEELER
    TWO_WHEELER
}

enum VehicleStatus {
    AVAILABLE
    BOOKED
    MAINTENANCE
}

note top of Vehicle #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - Core entities.**
    "**User** has userId, name, driving license.
    **Location** has address components.
    **Vehicle** has id, number, type, daily cost,
    and status (AVAILABLE/BOOKED/MAINTENANCE)."
end note

Vehicle --> VehicleType
Vehicle --> VehicleStatus
Store --> Location : at location >
VehicleRentalSystem o--> User : has users >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: VEHICLE INVENTORY — Thread-Safe (KEY)
' ====================================================================
class VehicleInventoryManager {
    - vehicles : map<int, Vehicle*>
    - vehicleBookingIds : map<int, vector<int>>
    - vehicleLocks : map<int, mutex*>
    - reservationRepository : ReservationRepository*
    --
    + addVehicle(vehicle) : void
    + getVehicle(vehicleId) : Vehicle*
    + setReservationRepository(repo) : void
    + isAvailable(vehicleId, from, to) : bool
    + reserve(vehicleId, reservationId, from, to) : bool
    + release(vehicleId, reservationId) : void
    + getAvailableVehicles(type, from, to) : vector<Vehicle*>
    - lockForVehicle(vehicleId) : mutex&
}

note top of VehicleInventoryManager #FFCDD2
    **STEP 3 - Inventory management. (KEY STEP)**
    "Manages all vehicles at a store.
    **Thread-safe** with per-vehicle mutex locks."

    "**isAvailable(vehicleId, from, to)**:
    Checks if vehicle has any overlapping
    reservations using DateInterval.overlaps()."

    "**reserve()**: lock_guard(mutex) ->
    check availability -> add reservationId
    to vehicle's booking list -> return true."

    "**release()**: removes reservationId
    from vehicle's booking list."

    "**getAvailableVehicles(FOUR_WHEELER, from, to)**:
    iterates all vehicles, filters by type + availability."

    "Per-vehicle mutex prevents two users from
    booking the same car simultaneously."
    **Pattern: Repository + Thread-Safe Locking**
end note

Store --> VehicleInventoryManager : owns >
VehicleInventoryManager o--> Vehicle : manages >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: RESERVATION LIFECYCLE
' ====================================================================
class Reservation {
    - reservationId : int
    - vehicleId : int
    - userId : int
    - dateBookedFrom : LocalDate
    - dateBookedTo : LocalDate
    - reservationType : ReservationType
    - reservationStatus : ReservationStatus
    --
    + getReservationId() : int
    + getVehicleId() : int
    + getUserId() : int
    + getDateBookedFrom() : LocalDate
    + getDateBookedTo() : LocalDate
    + getReservationType() : ReservationType
    + getReservationStatus() : ReservationStatus
    + setReservationStatus(status) : void
}

enum ReservationType {
    HOURLY
    DAILY
}

enum ReservationStatus {
    SCHEDULED
    IN_USE
    COMPLETED
    CANCELLED
}

class ReservationManager {
    - inventory : VehicleInventoryManager*
    - reservationRepository : ReservationRepository
    - reservationIdCounter : int = 20000
    --
    + findByID(reservationId) : Reservation*
    + createReservation(vehicleId, userId, from, to, type) : Reservation*
    + cancelReservation(reservationId) : void
    + startTrip(reservationId) : void
    + submitVehicle(reservationId) : void
    + remove(reservationId) : void
}

class ReservationRepository {
    - reservations : map<int, Reservation*>
    --
    + save(reservation) : void
    + findById(reservationId) : Reservation*
    + remove(reservationId) : void
    + getAll() : map<int, Reservation*>&
}

class LocalDate {
    + year : int
    + month : int
    + day : int
    --
    + isBefore(other) : bool
    + isAfter(other) : bool
    + daysBetween(other) : long
    + toString() : string
}

class DateInterval {
    - from : LocalDate
    - to : LocalDate
    --
    + DateInterval(from, to)
    + getFrom() : LocalDate
    + getTo() : LocalDate
    + overlaps(other) : bool
}

note top of ReservationManager #FFCDD2
    **STEP 4 - Reservation lifecycle.**
    "**ReservationManager** orchestrates:
    createReservation(): validate vehicle ->
    inventory.reserve() -> create Reservation
    (status=SCHEDULED) -> save to repository.

    startTrip(): set status = IN_USE.
    submitVehicle(): set status = COMPLETED,
    release vehicle in inventory.
    cancelReservation(): set status = CANCELLED,
    release vehicle."

    "**DateInterval.overlaps()** prevents
    double-booking by checking date overlap."
    **Patterns: Facade + Repository | SRP**
end note

Reservation --> ReservationType
Reservation --> ReservationStatus
Reservation --> LocalDate : from/to >
ReservationManager --> ReservationRepository : stores in >
ReservationManager --> VehicleInventoryManager : reserves via >
ReservationRepository o--> Reservation : manages >
Store --> ReservationManager : owns >
DateInterval --> LocalDate : wraps >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: BILLING — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
class Bill {
    - billId : int
    - reservationId : int
    - totalBillAmount : double
    - billPaid : bool
    --
    + getBillId() : int
    + getReservationId() : int
    + getTotalBillAmount() : double
    + isBillPaid() : bool
    + setBillPaid(paid) : void
}

abstract class BillingStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    --
    + {abstract} generateBill(reservation) : Bill*
}

class DailyBillingStrategy {
    - vehicleInventoryManager : VehicleInventoryManager*
    - billIdCounter : int = 5000
    --
    + generateBill(reservation) : Bill*
}

class BillManager {
    - billingStrategy : BillingStrategy*
    - bills : map<int, Bill*>
    --
    + BillManager(billingStrategy)
    + generateBill(reservation) : Bill*
    + getBill(billId) : Bill*
    + setBillingStrategy(strategy) : void
}

note top of BillingStrategy #FFE0B2
    **STEP 5 - Generate the bill.**
    "Car returned. How much to charge?
    **Strategy Pattern** — billing is pluggable."

    "**DailyBillingStrategy**: calculates
    days = dateBookedTo - dateBookedFrom.
    bill = days * vehicle.dailyRentalCost."

    "Add HourlyBillingStrategy? One new class.
    setBillingStrategy() swaps at runtime."

    "**BillManager** wraps the strategy and
    stores all generated bills (Repository)."
    **Pattern: Strategy + Repository | OCP, DIP**
end note

BillingStrategy <|-- DailyBillingStrategy
BillManager --> BillingStrategy : delegates >
BillManager o--> Bill : stores >
Store --> BillManager : owns >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: PAYMENT — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
class Payment {
    - paymentId : int
    - billId : int
    - amountPaid : double
    - paymentMode : PaymentMode
    - paymentDate : time_t
    --
    + getPaymentId() : int
    + getBillId() : int
    + getAmountPaid() : double
    + getPaymentMode() : PaymentMode
}

enum PaymentMode {
    CASH
    ONLINE
    UPI
}

abstract class PaymentStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    --
    + {abstract} processPayment(bill, amount) : Payment*
}

class UPIPaymentStrategy {
    - paymentIdCounter : int = 9000
    --
    + processPayment(bill, amount) : Payment*
}

class PaymentManager {
    - paymentStrategy : PaymentStrategy*
    - payments : map<int, Payment*>
    --
    + PaymentManager(paymentStrategy)
    + makePayment(bill, amount) : Payment*
    + getPaymentsForBill(billId) : vector<Payment*>
    + getPayment(paymentId) : Payment*
    + setPaymentStrategy(strategy) : void
}

note top of PaymentStrategy #D1C4E9
    **STEP 6 - Process payment.**
    "**Strategy Pattern** — payment method
    is pluggable. UPIPaymentStrategy creates
    Payment with mode=UPI."

    "Add CashPaymentStrategy, OnlinePaymentStrategy?
    One new class each. setPaymentStrategy()
    swaps at runtime."

    "**PaymentManager** wraps strategy and
    stores all payments (Repository)."
    **Pattern: Strategy + Repository | OCP, DIP**
end note

PaymentStrategy <|-- UPIPaymentStrategy
PaymentManager --> PaymentStrategy : delegates >
PaymentManager o--> Payment : stores >
Payment --> PaymentMode
Store --> PaymentManager : owns >


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "User searches store.getVehicles(FOUR_WHEELER, from, to)
    -> VehicleInventoryManager filters available cars -> user picks one
    -> store.createReservation() -> ReservationManager validates + reserves
    (mutex-protected) -> Reservation(SCHEDULED). User picks up car ->
    startTrip() -> IN_USE. Returns car -> submitVehicle() -> COMPLETED,
    vehicle released. store.generateBill() -> **DailyBillingStrategy**
    calculates days * rate. store.makePayment() -> **UPIPaymentStrategy**
    processes payment."

    "Key patterns: **Facade** (Store orchestrates everything), **Strategy**
    (x2: Billing + Payment), **Repository** (Reservation, Bill, Payment,
    Vehicle), **Thread-safe** (per-vehicle mutex). Clean layered architecture."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern |= Key Point |
    | 1 | VehicleRentalSystem -> Store (per-location facade) | Facade | Store composes all managers |
    | 2 | User, Location, Vehicle (type + status + daily cost) | Entity | Core domain objects |
    | 3 | VehicleInventoryManager: search, reserve, release (mutex) | Repository + Thread-safe | Per-vehicle mutex prevents double-booking |
    | 4 | Reservation: SCHEDULED -> IN_USE -> COMPLETED / CANCELLED | Lifecycle | DateInterval.overlaps() prevents conflicts |
    | 5 | DailyBillingStrategy: days * dailyRentalCost | Strategy (billing) | Pluggable billing algorithms |
    | 6 | UPIPaymentStrategy processes payment | Strategy (payment) | Pluggable payment methods |
    |  |  |  |  |
    | **Search + Book** = Steps 2-4 | **Return + Bill** = Step 5 | **Pay** = Step 6 | **Thread Safety** = Step 3 |
endlegend

@enduml
